
.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "December 2023" "Version 1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple Unix shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
The `simple_shell` command invokes a basic Unix shell. It interprets user commands, tokenizes input, and executes them. It offers various functionalities implemented across different files.

.SH OPTIONS
No command-line options are available.

.SH USAGE
To use the shell, execute the `simple_shell` command. Upon startup, the shell displays a prompt (`$`) where commands can be entered. To execute a command, type it and press Enter. To exit the shell, use the `exit` command or press Ctrl+D.

.SH FUNCTIONALITIES
The shell provides several functionalities across separate files:
- `simple_shell.c`: Main shell implementation.
- `Simple_Shell.h`: Header file with function prototypes and definitions.
- `Shell.h`: Header file with function prototypes and definitions.
- `simple_shell_arguments.c`: Handles command line arguments.
- `simple_shell_path.c`: Manages command execution with PATH handling.
- `Shell_built-in.c`: Implements the exit built-in command and the env built-in command. 

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Thetele Ramoonyane, Makhothi Tlali, and Relebohile Ramoshabe.

.SH SEE ALSO
For full documentation and detailed information, refer to the README.md file.

.SH BUGS
